The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                               IN THE CITY
                  
	 The CFL Premier Division clubs can recruit four foreigners, but only three will be allowed to take the field. It was also decided at a meeting on Monday that each side must field at least two under-19 players in the Premier Division. In another development, East Bengal have roped in Mohun Bagan midfielder Dharamjit Singh.           
	 Mohun Bagan have ruled out immediate plans of moving a higher court over Jose Ramirez Barretos case, but the club is offering the Brazilian all legal help. The law will take its own course of action and well help Barreto get justice, said a club official.           
	 City-boy Sanil Jagtiani accounted for the third seeded Maka Krishna Chaitanya in the first round of the boys singles under-12 event of the Infocus Technolgies AITA Talent Series tennis championships at the High Court Club lawns on Monday.                                                                                                                                                                       
